    "recap_headline": "Wright State University",
    "recap_text": "DAYTON-\nThe Wright State baseball team picked up a big 8-4 win over Milwaukee in Friday afternoon's series opener. The win moves the Raiders to 1-0 in Horizon League play, their third consecutive season starting conference play with a win.\nWright State (6-12, 1-0 HL) will be back in action tomorrow afternoon for game two of its three-game set with Milwaukee. First pitch at Nischwitz Stadium is slated for 2 p.m.\nCam Allen\ngot the start on the mound for the Raiders, pitching five innings, allowing three runs (two earned) on three hits while striking out five Panthers.\nAfter two scoreless frames,\nAndrew Duncan\nopened the scoring on Friday afternoon with a little league home run in the bottom of the third inning. The centerfielder ripped a two-run triple into the gap in left-center that scored\nPatrick Fultz\nand\nHunter Warren\n. After an error by the Panther third baseman, Duncan was able to come home and give the Raiders a three-run lead.\nMilwaukee would get one run back in the top of the fourth on a Dom Kibler opposite-field home run. The Raiders would answer right back in the bottom half of the frame when\nGus Gregory\ncame in to score on a\nBraylen Blomquist\nRBI single.\nThe Panthers would come back to tie the game with two runs in the fifth and one more in the sixth to tie the game at four entering the final three innings.\nJJ Thompson would pitch three stellar innings of relief to pick up his second win of the season. The left-hander allowed just one run on one hit while striking out three Panthers.\nJP Peltier\nwould regain the lead for the Raiders in the bottom of the seventh inning with a two-run double that scored Duncan and Fultz.\nFultz would give the Raiders some much-needed insurance in the bottom of the eighth, roping a two-run single through the left side of the infield to score\nZac Butler\nand\nCam Gilkerson\n.\nMichael Zielinski\ncame on to pitch the ninth for the Raiders. The freshman pitched a clean inning with two strikeouts to help seal the Wright State win.",
